channel.title: Is this done right?
channel.description: I dled JDK vs 13 my comp recognizes it. Iv got No-ip installed and registered and have made a host I have 43594 in windows fire wall but i dont use windows firewall I use norton which has its own firewall. (idk how to let stuff access through it) I have portforwarded..correctly I think..I port forwarded on my windows xp but it crashed and it saved it though but Im on a vista pc right now. Iv got a source When ppl try to logon it just says error connecting to server..it worked on my windows xp, could anyone help me and tell me what is wrong and how to fix this? sorry i suck at vista..used windows xp all my life. and if im missing any details please tell me and ill quote u back right away with them.

item.title: Is this done right?
item.dc:creator: @The_cook_from_runesc The cook from runescape
item.description:
@The_cook_from_runesc wrote:

Probably not, because I can’t help you if you don’t give me the damned internal IP addresses. What am I gonna do, come round to your house, access your wireless network and hope to god your firewall is down with all ports open so I can hack you?

And besides, you give your external IP address out to everyone who connects to your server which [regarding potential exploits] is infinitely more times dangerous than giving out your internal address.

But yeh I don’t really care if you don’t tell me… you’re the one who wants the help, I’m just trying to inform you of why I think you’re an idiot.
